				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Hail, Mages,
<br />

<br />
I posted this over at Graffe.com:
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">Quellious - which is considered the "top server" over on <a href="http://www.playerauctions.com" target="_blank" class="postlink">Player Auctions</a> - has been witnessing a steady and dramatic increase of prices on just about everything high-end -- from gear, to spells, to tradeskill items. However, I personally doubt very much that there is an exploit or a hack underway. For all of their delays, SOE has proven time and time again that it is extremely responsive, if not lightning-fast, in destroying exploits and patching holes that are flagrantly damaging, while leaving in annoying bugs that limit players (such as the current bug with the Sword of Xuzl). Also, if, in fact, the original poster had knowledge about this exploit, the best way to put a stop to it is to post about it and distribute this knowledge far and wide, so that everyone knows how to do the exploit. SOE would patch this matter up in a heartbeat, I am certain of it.
<br />

<br />
What I think is most likely happening is what <a href="http://www.mobhunter.com/article.jsp?articleid=-1389668485" target="_blank" class="postlink">a recent article on the rapidly-declining Mobhunter</a> described: possible assistance from GMs from within SOE, or monopolization of zones. Specifically, consider Bards in Nadox. A single bard can swarm kite over fifty mobs and kill them all for insane amounts of experience, and equally outrageous loot. On a recent trip to Nadox on Quellious, I verified this practice with my own eyes -- and in fact, the bard had five other unattended characters just sitting in group, by the zone, doing nothing but raking in the experience. This is precisely how, I believe, people are offering powerleveling services and farming in massive amounts of platinum - through monopolization of underused content. Check out Nadox with your own eyes sometime on your server: you would be shocked.
<br />

<br />
Kaelon</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
