			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">A couple of observations to make here:
<br />

<br />
    1) Lot's of plat on the market - This could be caused by a number of things. One would be "recycling". The people selling bulk PP are often the same people selling the very high end gear. By participating, people are feeding this machine, where plat is never taken out of the market, but new gear, and additional platinum is introduced. <span style="font-weight: bold">IF</span> there is a duplication bug, then this only compounds the problem. The abuser could create a "ton" of plat, buy all the top gear, and still have more plat to sell. "Normal" players lose the means to purchase items at normal prices. 
<br />

<br />
    2) Power Levelling - It's probably not economical for these people to keep on making plat if the market has bottomed out. Rather than cutting all of their "helpers", they've simply been redeployed for PL duties. Note that this is a limited time offer, not because of a levelling exploit, but because whatever had been allowing all of this platinum appear will either be gone with the next patch or the platinum itself will run out by the end of the year. Allow a few more weeks for the platinum to work its way out of the creator's coffers, and the PL people will be diverted back to plat farming.
<br />

<br />
There's really no reason to point a finger at Sony employees for this, and I can't believe that a duplication bug could exist for the past month without people finding out about it.
<br />

<br />
Its much more likely that a few higher end guilds on certain servers decided to join forces with Yantis and dump a lot of money out of their guild bank's onto the market. All it would take is a few guild bankers/leaders to quietly agree to start dumping plat and a few high end items, and the market is easily cornered. Disposable reagents don't cost nearly as much as some of these guilds can rake in, and its been pointed out before that most folks that have reached the EP don't have much need for plat anymore. The new character transfer process helps this along, as excess plat can move between servers.
<br />

<br />
There are lots of logical reasons for this kind of thing to happen. All the more reason for SOE to consider adding a Guild housing/banking mechanism to the game, so this kind of activity is more easily monitored by players.  
<br />

<br />
Just my 2cp, which apparently doesn't amount to as much as it used to. ~<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=381929&resize=true" target="_blank" class="postlink">Naladini Dreamfyre</a>
<br />
Arch Mage of 61 Seasons - <a href="http://www.stormhammer.org/forums" target="_blank" class="postlink">Stormhammer*</a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
