				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">This problem has hit every server.  I can say this is really bad for EQ.
<br />

<br />
I used to be a Diablo 2 player.  The game was utterly ripped apart by dupers.  An item that used to be worth 5-10 dollars in real life(this item was chosen as the currency of the game as Gold was useless) is now gived away because players have so many and need to make room in their banks.  Basically worth nothing at all.
<br />

<br />
As for EQ - I don't see why Yantis would be behind the platinum, as the inflation hurts his prices.  However I can see him behind the powerlevelling because the value of exp will not change so long as the same amount of people play EQ.
<br />

<br />
I don't know where the platinum could have come from.  But I will say this.  <span style="font-weight: bold">It is absolutely impossible for this much platinum to come from the game in such a short period of time</span>.  People have been playing EQ for 4 years, and, when they kill stuff, <span style="font-weight: bold">platinum drops and is cycled into the server's economy</span>.  There is no way that in 2 months this much platinum could be dropped or obtained from NPC's.  It simply has to be a bug, hack, exploit, or 3rd party program.
<br />

<br />
GM participation in this - although I don't like the idea of GM's being behind this, it seems to me to be the only logical explanation at the moment.  Sony's refusal to take action only adds to this suspicion.<br />_________________<br />"Guess what?  Magelo is down again!"
